        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/9de053/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-05-22T21:05:57.103Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Currently the conversation tab have a redpill to indicate when there are notifications.<br>\nIt would be more relaxing to change the operation of the redpill.</p>\n<p>With the extension of users and fonctionality in Signal, the app is used for multiple purposes :</p>\n<ul>\n<li>For personnal conversation, work, or activism, etc.</li>\n<li>For one to one conversation, groupe conversation, or channel.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The conversation folders help to organize all of those conversation, but remain the stress and FOMO of the redpill in the bottom of the app for all notifications.<br>\nSome notifications are not as important to trigger the redpill on the tab (ex: notifications from channels (read only), or from some groupes).</p>\n<p>It would be a progress for the use of Signal as a chat app for many purposes (friends, work, activism, etc.) if it’d be possible to remove this stressfull trigger warning at the bottom bar for each new notification.</p>\n<p>Some thought as solution:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>To be able to remove a conversation from the trigger of the redpill;</li>\n<li>To exclude all mute conversations for the redpill;</li>\n<li>To add as a new rule for conversation folder to didn’t trigger the redpill for all conversation in it;</li>\n<li>Remove the redpill entirely;</li>\n<li>Change the color of the redpill;</li>\n<li>Add a new tab at the bottom for “Silent conversations” / “News” to move in all conversations we don’t want to trigger the redpill (so no redpill for this tab).</li>\n</ul>",
